  "detailed_description": "<span class=\"bb_img_ctn\"><img class=\"bb_img\" src=\"https://shared.akamai.steamstatic.com/store_item_assets/steam/apps/2431070/extras/903cc7fd66e446c19b12abf0db34a7d5.avif?t=1732908694\" width=64 height=64 /></span> <span class=\"bb_img_ctn\"><img class=\"bb_img\" src=\"https://shared.akamai.steamstatic.com/store_item_assets/steam/apps/2431070/extras/396587d6d10c37cc972eca55a83cd18e.webp?t=1732908694\" width=128 height=48 /></span><br><br>The 98xx was an old computer OS from the 90s that’s recently been discovered after many years of being lost. There are still a few working files within the OS that can be explored, but there are a few unexpected glitches. One program in particular which goes by the name of \"Jumping Julian\" on the surface seems like your typical 2D platformer, but as the game goes on, weird things start to happen. Play at your own risk!<br><br>List of applications:<br><br>GAMES:<br>-Jumping Julian.exe<br>-Puzzle Patterns<br>-BallPopper<br>-Questions/Answers Game<br>-Talking Gerald.exe<br>-Tank Blast<br>-Asteroid Blast<br>-Matching Game<br>-Dancing with Darcy.exe<br>-Math Game<br>-Kingdom Quest<br>-Shape Game<br><br>SOFTWARE:<br>-Pixel Paint<br>-TypeWriter<br>-Photo Editor<br>-Video Editor<br><br>MISCELLANEOUS:<br>-Surfur (Web Browser)<br>-VidPlayer<br>-Documents<br>-Photo Gallery<br>-AudioPlayer<br>-DialCaller<br>-BookReader<br>-Settings<br>-Security<br><br>© Mirez Incorporated - 1998 <br><br><span class=\"bb_img_ctn\"><video class=\"bb_img\" autoplay muted loop playsinline crossorigin=\"anonymous\" poster=\"https://shared.akamai.steamstatic.com/store_item_assets/steam/apps/2431070/extras/e9c8c7c5863b62a4be2bff92e441f6b2.poster.avif?t=1732908694\" width=128 height=128 ><source src=\"https://shared.akamai.steamstatic.com/store_item_assets/steam/apps/2431070/extras/e9c8c7c5863b62a4be2bff92e441f6b2.webm?t=1732908694\" type=\"video/webm; codecs=vp9\"></video></span> <span class=\"bb_img_ctn\"><video class=\"bb_img\" autoplay muted loop playsinline crossorigin=\"anonymous\" poster=\"https://shared.akamai.steamstatic.com/store_item_assets/steam/apps/2431070/extras/e8993abb7de8882b4f93a7fbfbbd6913.poster.avif?t=1732908694\" width=128 height=128 ><source src=\"https://shared.akamai.steamstatic.com/store_item_assets/steam/apps/2431070/extras/e8993abb7de8882b4f93a7fbfbbd6913.webm?t=1732908694\" type=\"video/webm; codecs=vp9\"></video></span> <span class=\"bb_img_ctn\"><video class=\"bb_img\" autoplay muted loop playsinline crossorigin=\"anonymous\" poster=\"https://shared.akamai.steamstatic.com/store_item_assets/steam/apps/2431070/extras/e620d57cd5bba123adb6899cb169b186.poster.avif?t=1732908694\" width=96 height=96 ><source src=\"https://shared.akamai.steamstatic.com/store_item_assets/steam/apps/2431070/extras/e620d57cd5bba123adb6899cb169b186.webm?t=1732908694\" type=\"video/webm; codecs=vp9\"></video></span>",
  "about_the_game": "<span class=\"bb_img_ctn\"><img class=\"bb_img\" src=\"https://shared.akamai.steamstatic.com/store_item_assets/steam/apps/2431070/extras/903cc7fd66e446c19b12abf0db34a7d5.avif?t=1732908694\" width=64 height=64 /></span> <span class=\"bb_img_ctn\"><img class=\"bb_img\" src=\"https://shared.akamai.steamstatic.com/store_item_assets/steam/apps/2431070/extras/396587d6d10c37cc972eca55a83cd18e.webp?t=1732908694\" width=128 height=48 /></span><br><br>The 98xx was an old computer OS from the 90s that’s recently been discovered after many years of being lost. There are still a few working files within the OS that can be explored, but there are a few unexpected glitches. One program in particular which goes by the name of \"Jumping Julian\" on the surface seems like your typical 2D platformer, but as the game goes on, weird things start to happen. Play at your own risk!<br><br>List of applications:<br><br>GAMES:<br>-Jumping Julian.exe<br>-Puzzle Patterns<br>-BallPopper<br>-Questions/Answers Game<br>-Talking Gerald.exe<br>-Tank Blast<br>-Asteroid Blast<br>-Matching Game<br>-Dancing with Darcy.exe<br>-Math Game<br>-Kingdom Quest<br>-Shape Game<br><br>SOFTWARE:<br>-Pixel Paint<br>-TypeWriter<br>-Photo Editor<br>-Video Editor<br><br>MISCELLANEOUS:<br>-Surfur (Web Browser)<br>-VidPlayer<br>-Documents<br>-Photo Gallery<br>-AudioPlayer<br>-DialCaller<br>-BookReader<br>-Settings<br>-Security<br><br>© Mirez Incorporated - 1998 <br><br><span class=\"bb_img_ctn\"><video class=\"bb_img\" autoplay muted loop playsinline crossorigin=\"anonymous\" poster=\"https://shared.akamai.steamstatic.com/store_item_assets/steam/apps/2431070/extras/e9c8c7c5863b62a4be2bff92e441f6b2.poster.avif?t=1732908694\" width=128 height=128 ><source src=\"https://shared.akamai.steamstatic.com/store_item_assets/steam/apps/2431070/extras/e9c8c7c5863b62a4be2bff92e441f6b2.webm?t=1732908694\" type=\"video/webm; codecs=vp9\"></video></span> <span class=\"bb_img_ctn\"><video class=\"bb_img\" autoplay mu